+6. [P2] Submit-error fallback text falsely claims the order was saved вҖ” the cart error state at [CartView.jsx](/C:/Dev/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/base/CartView.jsx#L1233) still falls back to `Р’Р°СҲ Р·Р°РәР°Р· СҒРҫС…СҖР°РҪС‘РҪ. РҹРҫРҝСҖРҫРұСғР№СӮРө СҒРҪРҫРІР°`, which is the same misleading copy previously tracked in `BUGS.md` as PM-038. If the locale key is missing or stale, the UI tells guests the order exists when it may not. FIX: replace that fallback with neutral retry text matching the safer copy already defined in [x.jsx](/C:/Dev/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/base/x.jsx#L407).
+7. [P3] Reward-email microcopy still bypasses i18n вҖ” the reward-email form in [CartView.jsx](/C:/Dev/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/base/CartView.jsx#L518) hardcodes `"email@example.com"` and `'...'` instead of using translation keys. This leaks English-only copy into localized menus. FIX: move the placeholder and saving/loading text into `t()/tr()` keys, for example `form.email_placeholder` and `common.saving`.
